== Description ==

The [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintEqualRadius.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintEqualRadius|Equal radius]] command constrains the radius of a 2D circle or arc made with [[Image:Workbench_Draft.svg|16px]] [[Draft_Workbench|Draft Workbench]] tools in relation with a [[Image:Assembly_Workplane.svg|16px]] workplane.

It links the radius of the 2D circle or arc with the radius of another 2D circle or arc.

The radius value of the first selected circle or arc equals the radius value of the second circle or arc.

== Usage ==

# Select a 2D '''circle''' or '''arc''' to constrain.
# Select another 2D '''circle''' or '''arc''' to read its radius value.
# Activate the [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintEqualRadius.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintEqualRadius|Equal radius]] command using the:
#* {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_ConstraintEqualRadius.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintEqualRadius|Equal radius]]}} button.
# Press the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly3_workbench_icon.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ResolveConstraints|Solve constraints]]}} or the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_QuickSolve.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_QuickSolve|Quick solve]]}} button to recompute 
:: (if {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_AutoRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_AutoRecompute|Auto recompute]]}} and {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_SmartRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_SmartRecompute|Smart recompute]]}} are disabled).


